  "prompt": "Septoplasty at fortis?",
  "response": "Fortis Healthcare is a well-known network of hospitals in India that offers a variety of medical services, including ENT (Ear, Nose, and Throat) procedures like septoplasty. Septoplasty is a surgical procedure to correct a deviated septum, which can help improve breathing and alleviate other related issues such as nasal congestion.\n\nIf you are considering septoplasty at Fortis, here are a few points to keep in mind:\n\n1. **Consultation**: It's essential to consult an ENT specialist to discuss your symptoms and determine if septoplasty is the right option for you.\n\n2. **Facilities**: Fortis hospitals are equipped with modern facilities and experienced medical staff, which can provide a comfortable environment for both the procedure and recovery.\n\n3. **Preoperative Evaluation**: You might undergo several tests and evaluations prior to surgery to assess your health and ensure you're a good candidate for the procedure.\n\n4. **Procedure Details**: Septoplasty is typically performed under local or general anesthesia and usually takes about 30 to 90 minutes.\n\n5. **Postoperative Care**: After the surgery, you'll receive instructions about care, potential side effects, and when to follow up with your doctor.\n\n6. **Insurance and Costs**: Check with your insurance provider to see if septoplasty is covered, and inquire about costs and payment options at Fortis.\n\nFor detailed information, specific hospital policies, or to schedule an appointment, it's best to contact the nearest Fortis Healthcare facility directly or visit their official website.",
